The paper deals with interpretability of deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The use of decision trees for rule extraction is also a well-established technique in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of Rectified Linear Unit activation functions, which is commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
